{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1111,"text":"Imagine that you're a pig farmer."},{"time":4232,"text":"You live on a small farm\nin the Philippines."},{"time":7101,"text":"Your animals are your family's\nsole source of income --"},{"time":10784,"text":"as long as they're healthy."},{"time":12709,"text":"You know that any day,"},{"time":14103,"text":"one of your pigs can catch the flu,"},{"time":16347,"text":"the swine flu."},{"time":17718,"text":"Living in tight quarters,\none pig coughing and sneezing"},{"time":21013,"text":"may soon lead to the next pig\ncoughing and sneezing,"},{"time":23977,"text":"until an outbreak of swine flu\nhas taken over your farm."},{"time":27841,"text":"If it's a bad enough virus,"},{"time":29554,"text":"the health of your herd may be gone\nin the blink of an eye."},{"time":33256,"text":"If you called in a veterinarian,"},{"time":34924,"text":"he or she would visit your farm\nand take samples"},{"time":37431,"text":"from your pigs' noses and mouths."},{"time":39279,"text":"But then they would have to drive\nback into the city"},{"time":42130,"text":"to test those samples\nin their central lab."},{"time":45556,"text":"Two weeks later,\nyou'd hear back the results."},{"time":48601,"text":"Two weeks may be just enough time\nfor infection to spread"},{"time":52711,"text":"and take away your way of life."}]},{"cues":[{"time":55616,"text":"But it doesn't have to be that way."},{"time":57411,"text":"Today, farmers can take\nthose samples themselves."},{"time":60692,"text":"They can jump right into the pen\nand swab their pigs' noses and mouths"},{"time":64463,"text":"with a little filter paper,"},{"time":66288,"text":"place that little filter paper\nin a tiny tube,"},{"time":69525,"text":"and mix it with some chemicals\nthat will extract genetic material"},{"time":73430,"text":"from their pigs' noses and mouths."},{"time":75367,"text":"And without leaving their farms,"},{"time":77316,"text":"they take a drop of that genetic material"},{"time":79638,"text":"and put it into a little analyzer\nsmaller than a shoebox,"},{"time":83872,"text":"program it to detect DNA or RNA\nfrom the swine flu virus,"},{"time":88497,"text":"and within one hour get back the results,\nvisualize the results."},{"time":93247,"text":"This reality is possible"},{"time":95227,"text":"because today we're living in the era\nof personal DNA technology."},{"time":99172,"text":"Every one of us can actually\ntest DNA ourselves."}]},{"cues":[{"time":103448,"text":"DNA is the fundamental molecule\nthe carries genetic instructions"},{"time":107211,"text":"that help build the living world."},{"time":110052,"text":"Humans have DNA."},{"time":111814,"text":"Pigs have DNA."},{"time":113410,"text":"Even bacteria and some\nviruses have DNA too."},{"time":116928,"text":"The genetic instructions encoded in DNA\ninform how our bodies develop,"},{"time":121176,"text":"grow, function."},{"time":122908,"text":"And in many cases, that same information\ncan trigger disease."},{"time":126915,"text":"Your genetic information"},{"time":128710,"text":"is strung into a long and twisted\nmolecule, the DNA double helix,"},{"time":132424,"text":"that has over three billion letters,"},{"time":134896,"text":"beginning to end."},{"time":136484,"text":"But the lines that carry\nmeaningful information"},{"time":139728,"text":"are usually very short --"},{"time":141317,"text":"a few dozen to several\nthousand letters long."},{"time":144363,"text":"So when we're looking to answer\na question based on DNA,"},{"time":147534,"text":"we actually don't need to read"},{"time":149491,"text":"all those three billion\nletters, typically."},{"time":151984,"text":"That would be like getting hungry at night"},{"time":154245,"text":"and having to flip through\nthe whole phone book"},{"time":156659,"text":"from cover to cover,"},{"time":157938,"text":"pausing at every line,"},{"time":159537,"text":"just to find the nearest pizza joint."}]},{"cues":[{"time":161546,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":162722,"text":"Luckily, three decades ago,"},{"time":165283,"text":"humans started to invent tools"},{"time":167235,"text":"that can find any specific line\nof genetic information."},{"time":170766,"text":"These DNA machines are wonderful."},{"time":172979,"text":"They can find any line in DNA."},{"time":175732,"text":"But once they find it,"},{"time":177060,"text":"that DNA is still tiny, and surrounded\nby so much other DNA,"},{"time":182535,"text":"that what these machines then do\nis copy the target gene,"},{"time":187201,"text":"and one copy piles on top of another,"},{"time":189466,"text":"millions and millions\nand millions of copies,"},{"time":191655,"text":"until that gene stands out\nagainst the rest;"},{"time":194665,"text":"until we can visualize it,"},{"time":196872,"text":"interpret it, read it, understand it,"},{"time":199439,"text":"until we can answer:"},{"time":200741,"text":"Does my pig have the flu?"},{"time":203914,"text":"Or other questions buried in our own DNA:"},{"time":207435,"text":"Am I at risk of cancer?"},{"time":210505,"text":"Am I of Irish descent?"},{"time":212623,"text":"Is that child my son?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":215672,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":218537,"text":"This ability to make copies of DNA,\nas simple as it sounds,"},{"time":223235,"text":"has transformed our world."},{"time":224550,"text":"Scientists use it every day\nto detect and address disease,"},{"time":229586,"text":"to create innovative medicines,"},{"time":232098,"text":"to modify foods,"},{"time":234158,"text":"to assess whether our food is safe to eat"},{"time":236158,"text":"or whether it's contaminated\nwith deadly bacteria."},{"time":239578,"text":"Even judges use the output\nof these machines in court"},{"time":242446,"text":"to decide whether someone is innocent\nor guilty based on DNA evidence."},{"time":247044,"text":"The inventor of this DNA-copying technique"},{"time":249481,"text":"was awarded the Nobel Prize\nin Chemistry in 1993."},{"time":253831,"text":"But for 30 years,"},{"time":255007,"text":"the power of genetic analysis\nhas been confined to the ivory tower,"},{"time":258864,"text":"or bigwig PhD scientist work."},{"time":262333,"text":"Well, several companies around the world"},{"time":264459,"text":"are working on making\nthis same technology accessible"},{"time":268331,"text":"to everyday people like the pig farmer,"},{"time":271386,"text":"like you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":272759,"text":"I cofounded one of these companies."},{"time":275367,"text":"Three years ago,"},{"time":276542,"text":"together with a fellow biologist\nand friend of mine,"},{"time":279553,"text":"Zeke Alvarez Saavedra,"},{"time":281157,"text":"we decided to make personal DNA machines"},{"time":283796,"text":"that anyone could use."},{"time":285957,"text":"Our goal was to bring DNA science\nto more people in new places."},{"time":289892,"text":"We started working in our basements."},{"time":292077,"text":"We had a simple question:"},{"time":294154,"text":"What could the world look like"},{"time":295929,"text":"if everyone could analyze DNA?"},{"time":298380,"text":"We were curious,"},{"time":300142,"text":"as curious as you would have been\nif I had shown you this picture in 1980."}]},{"cues":[{"time":305092,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":306401,"text":"You would have thought, \"Wow!"},{"time":308216,"text":"I can now call\nmy Aunt Glenda from the car"},{"time":310843,"text":"and wish her a happy birthday."},{"time":312753,"text":"I can call anyone, anytime."},{"time":315055,"text":"This is the future!\""},{"time":317801,"text":"Little did you know,"},{"time":319281,"text":"you would tap on that phone\nto make dinner reservations"},{"time":321910,"text":"for you and Aunt Glenda\nto celebrate together."},{"time":324358,"text":"With another tap,\nyou'd be ordering her gift."},{"time":326912,"text":"And yet one more tap,"},{"time":328418,"text":"and you'd be \"liking\"\nAuntie Glenda on Facebook."},{"time":330754,"text":"And all of this,\nwhile sitting on the toilet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":333122,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":335320,"text":"It is notoriously hard to predict\nwhere new technology might take us."},{"time":340607,"text":"And the same is true\nfor personal DNA technology today."}]},{"cues":[{"time":345040,"text":"For example, I could never have imagined"},{"time":348133,"text":"that a truffle farmer, of all people,"},{"time":350678,"text":"would use personal DNA machines."},{"time":353267,"text":"Dr. Paul Thomas grows\ntruffles for a living."},{"time":356582,"text":"We see him pictured here,"},{"time":358313,"text":"holding the first UK-cultivated truffle\nin his hands, on one of his farms."},{"time":364179,"text":"Truffles are this delicacy"},{"time":365699,"text":"that stems from a fungus\ngrowing on the roots of living trees."},{"time":369786,"text":"And it's a rare fungus."},{"time":371437,"text":"Some species may fetch 3,000,\n7,000, or more dollars per kilogram."},{"time":377968,"text":"I learned from Paul"},{"time":379385,"text":"that the stakes for a truffle farmer\ncan be really high."},{"time":382296,"text":"When he sources new truffles\nto grow on his farms,"},{"time":385534,"text":"he's exposed to the threat\nof knockoffs --"},{"time":388086,"text":"truffles that look and feel\nlike the real thing,"},{"time":391566,"text":"but they're of lower quality."},{"time":393092,"text":"But even to a trained eye like Paul's,"},{"time":395545,"text":"even when looked at under a microscope,"},{"time":397651,"text":"these truffles can pass for authentic."},{"time":399826,"text":"So in order to grow\nthe highest quality truffles,"},{"time":403776,"text":"the ones that chefs\nall over the world will fight over,"},{"time":407039,"text":"Paul has to use DNA analysis."},{"time":410594,"text":"Isn't that mind-blowing?"},{"time":412364,"text":"I bet you will never look\nat that black truffle risotto again"},{"time":415688,"text":"without thinking of its genes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":417382,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":419710,"text":"But personal DNA machines\ncan also save human lives."},{"time":425045,"text":"Professor Ian Goodfellow is a virologist\nat the University of Cambridge."},{"time":429589,"text":"Last year he traveled to Sierra Leone."},{"time":432267,"text":"When the Ebola outbreak\nbroke out in Western Africa,"},{"time":436213,"text":"he quickly realized that doctors there\nlacked the basic tools"},{"time":440049,"text":"to detect and combat disease."},{"time":442216,"text":"Results could take\nup to a week to come back --"},{"time":445274,"text":"that's way too long for the patients\nand the families who are suffering."},{"time":450157,"text":"Ian decided to move his lab\ninto Makeni, Sierra Leone."},{"time":455194,"text":"Here we see Ian Goodfellow"},{"time":457343,"text":"moving over 10 tons of equipment\ninto a pop-up tent"},{"time":461435,"text":"that he would equip to detect\nand diagnose the virus"},{"time":465135,"text":"and sequence it within 24 hours."},{"time":468250,"text":"But here's a surprise:"},{"time":470053,"text":"the same equipment that Ian could use\nat his lab in the UK"},{"time":474199,"text":"to sequence and diagnose Ebola,"},{"time":476814,"text":"just wouldn't work under these conditions."},{"time":478971,"text":"We're talking 35 Celsius heat\nand over 90 percent humidity here."},{"time":484153,"text":"But instead, Ian could use\npersonal DNA machines"},{"time":487061,"text":"small enough to be placed\nin front of the air-conditioning unit"},{"time":490435,"text":"to keep sequencing the virus"},{"time":492390,"text":"and keep saving lives."}]},{"cues":[{"time":493989,"text":"This may seem like\nan extreme place for DNA analysis,"},{"time":497050,"text":"but let's move on to an even\nmore extreme environment:"},{"time":500850,"text":"outer space."},{"time":502633,"text":"Let's talk about DNA analysis in space."},{"time":505657,"text":"When astronauts live aboard\nthe International Space Station,"},{"time":508801,"text":"they're orbiting the planet\n250 miles high."},{"time":512448,"text":"They're traveling\nat 17,000 miles per hour."},{"time":515274,"text":"Picture that --"},{"time":516456,"text":"you're seeing 15 sunsets\nand sunrises every day."},{"time":520817,"text":"You're also living in microgravity,"},{"time":522713,"text":"floating."},{"time":523905,"text":"And under these conditions,\nour bodies can do funky things."},{"time":527091,"text":"One of these things is that\nour immune systems get suppressed,"},{"time":531857,"text":"making astronauts more prone to infection."}]},{"cues":[{"time":535856,"text":"A 16-year-old girl,"},{"time":537793,"text":"a high school student from New York,\nAnna-Sophia Boguraev,"},{"time":541648,"text":"wondered whether changes\nto the DNA of astronauts"},{"time":544541,"text":"could be related\nto this immune suppression,"},{"time":546988,"text":"and through a science competition\ncalled \"Genes In Space,\""},{"time":550381,"text":"Anna-Sophia designed an experiment\nto test this hypothesis"},{"time":554312,"text":"using a personal DNA machine\naboard the International Space Station."},{"time":559463,"text":"Here we see Anna-Sophia\non April 8, 2016, in Cape Canaveral,"},{"time":565186,"text":"watching her experiment launch\nto the International Space Station."},{"time":569273,"text":"That cloud of smoke is the rocket"},{"time":571828,"text":"that brought Anna-Sophia's experiment\nto the International Space Station,"},{"time":576547,"text":"where, three days later,"},{"time":578500,"text":"astronaut Tim Peake\ncarried out her experiment --"},{"time":582272,"text":"in microgravity."},{"time":584175,"text":"Personal DNA machines are now\naboard the International Space Station,"},{"time":587955,"text":"where they can help monitor\nliving conditions"},{"time":590566,"text":"and protect the lives of astronauts."}]},{"cues":[{"time":593938,"text":"A 16-year-old designing a DNA experiment"},{"time":597803,"text":"to protect the lives of astronauts"},{"time":599740,"text":"may seem like a rarity,\nthe mark of a child genius."},{"time":603784,"text":"Well, to me, it signals\nsomething bigger:"},{"time":606378,"text":"that DNA technology is finally\nwithin the reach of every one of you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":612999,"text":"A few years ago,"},{"time":614730,"text":"a college student armed\nwith a personal computer"},{"time":617937,"text":"could code an app,"},{"time":619112,"text":"an app that is now a social network\nwith more than one billion users."},{"time":623933,"text":"Could we be moving into a world"},{"time":625917,"text":"of one personal DNA machine in every home?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":629966,"text":"I know families who are already\nliving in this reality."},{"time":633767,"text":"The Daniels family, for example,"},{"time":635689,"text":"set up a DNA lab in the basement\nof their suburban Chicago home."},{"time":640904,"text":"This is not a family\nmade of PhD scientists."},{"time":644656,"text":"This is a family like any other."},{"time":646790,"text":"They just like to spend time together\ndoing fun, creative things."},{"time":650869,"text":"By day, Brian is an executive\nat a private equity firm."},{"time":655137,"text":"At night and on weekends,\nhe experiments with DNA"},{"time":658066,"text":"alongside his kids, ages seven and nine,"},{"time":660987,"text":"as a way to explore the living world."},{"time":663480,"text":"Last time I called them,"},{"time":665178,"text":"they were checking out homegrown produce\nfrom the backyard garden."},{"time":669090,"text":"They were testing tomatoes\nthat they had picked,"},{"time":671411,"text":"taking the flesh of their skin,\nputting it in a test tube,"},{"time":674215,"text":"mixing it with chemicals to extract DNA"},{"time":676321,"text":"and then using their home DNA copier"},{"time":679823,"text":"to test those tomatoes\nfor genetically engineered traits."}]},{"cues":[{"time":684883,"text":"For the Daniels family,"},{"time":686434,"text":"the personal DNA machine\nis like the chemistry set"},{"time":689357,"text":"for the 21st century."},{"time":691375,"text":"Most of us may not yet\nbe diagnosing genetic conditions"},{"time":695261,"text":"in our kitchen sinks"},{"time":697123,"text":"or doing at-home paternity testing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":699365,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":700414,"text":"But we've definitely reached\na point in history"},{"time":702658,"text":"where every one of you could actually\nget hands-on with DNA"},{"time":708491,"text":"in your kitchen."},{"time":709946,"text":"You could copy, paste and analyze DNA"},{"time":713157,"text":"and extract meaningful\ninformation from it."},{"time":716394,"text":"And it's at times like this\nthat profound transformation"},{"time":719275,"text":"is bound to happen;"},{"time":720898,"text":"moments when a transformative,\npowerful technology"},{"time":724174,"text":"that was before limited\nto a select few in the ivory tower,"},{"time":727820,"text":"finally becomes within the reach\nof every one of us,"},{"time":731951,"text":"from farmers to schoolchildren."},{"time":734772,"text":"Think about the moment"},{"time":735963,"text":"when phones stopped being\nplugged into the wall by cords,"},{"time":739864,"text":"or when computers left the mainframe"},{"time":742183,"text":"and entered your home or your office."}]},{"cues":[{"time":745574,"text":"The ripples of the personal DNA revolution"},{"time":748421,"text":"may be hard to predict,"},{"time":749972,"text":"but one thing is certain:"},{"time":751613,"text":"revolutions don't go backwards,"},{"time":754029,"text":"and DNA technology is already spreading\nfaster than our imagination."}]},{"cues":[{"time":758318,"text":"So if you're curious,"},{"time":760241,"text":"get up close and personal\nwith DNA -- today."},{"time":763480,"text":"It is in our DNA to be curious."}]},{"cues":[{"time":766095,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":767134,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":768318,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}